    {
      "title": "Noun of Single Instance (اسم المرة)",
      "titleArabic": "اسم المرة",
      "content": [
        "The noun of single instance (اسم المرة) indicates that an action occurred once.",
        "For Form I verbs, it follows the pattern فَعْلَة: ضَرْبَة (one strike), جَلْسَة (one sitting)."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern for Form I: فَعْلَة",
        "ضَرَبَ → ضَرْبَة (one strike/hit)",
        "جَلَسَ → جَلْسَة (one sitting/session)",
        "نَظَرَ → نَظْرَة (one glance)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "ضَرَبَهُ ضَرْبَةً وَاحِدَةً", "english": "He hit him one strike" },
        { "arabic": "نَظَرْتُ إِلَيْهِ نَظْرَةً", "english": "I glanced at him once" },
        { "arabic": "جَلَسْنَا جَلْسَةً طَوِيلَةً", "english": "We sat for one long session" },
        { "arabic": "أَكَلَ أَكْلَةً كَبِيرَةً", "english": "He ate one large meal" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Noun of Single Instance for Derived Forms",
      "titleArabic": "اسم المرة للأفعال المزيدة",
      "content": [
        "For derived verb forms (II-X), add ة to the masdar to form the noun of single instance.",
        "If the masdar already ends in ة, add واحدة for clarification."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Form II: تَعْلِيم → تَعْلِيمَة (one teaching)",
        "Form III: مُسَاعَدَة → مُسَاعَدَة وَاحِدَة (one help)",
        "Form IV: إِرْسَال → إِرْسَالَة (one sending)",
        "Form X: اِسْتِغْفَار → اِسْتِغْفَارَة (one seeking forgiveness)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "عَلَّمَهُ تَعْلِيمَةً مُفِيدَةً", "english": "He taught him one useful lesson" },
        { "arabic": "سَاعَدْتُهُ مُسَاعَدَةً وَاحِدَةً", "english": "I helped him once" },
        { "arabic": "أَرْسَلَ إِرْسَالَةً وَاحِدَةً", "english": "He sent one message" },
        { "arabic": "اِسْتَغْفَرَ اللهَ اِسْتِغْفَارَةً", "english": "He sought forgiveness from Allah once" }
      ]
    }
  ],
